09:   seat_dispatch_timeout: \"Record the seat as failed for the iteration; merge surviving seats (agreement degrades gracefully); retry the seat once next iteration.\"\n\n  Line 828:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n\n  Line 840:     - skip_convergence_check\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-git/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 166: Prompt: `Start a login-timeout feature in an isolated worktree, keep main clean, and report the worktree path, branch, and verdict.`\n\n  Line 168: Expected signals: Main status is unchanged; new worktree appears in `git worktree list`; branch is `fix/login-timeout`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml:\n  Line 269:   fallback: { timeout_s: 60, on_timeout: \"continue with available\", on_all_fail: \"single-agent mode\" }\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:\n  Line 40:       - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-spec-memory IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_health --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n\n  Line 93:       - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-code-index IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n\n  Line 110:       - 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"{loop_type}\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n\n  Line 114:       - \"deep-research convergence drift\"\n\n  Line 134:       - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-skill-advisor IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --workspace-root \"$PWD\" --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n\n  Line 149:       - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-skill-advisor IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --workspace-root \"$PWD\" --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"convergenceThreshold|convergence|computeLineageTimeoutMs|timeout|fanout_lineage_artifact_dir|step_fanout_spawn|fanout-run","time":{"start":1782884246423,"end":1782884246436}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b1b14e4de1f56e8016a44a79647e08191949d5b704d4ec1c3"}},"id":"prt_f1c2ea366001B2DF9yE7wxg1C6","sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","messageID":"msg_f1c2e54d40016ostd7nghcJ7Z6"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782884246849,"sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","part":{"id":"prt_f1c2ea53d001f8nRf21BGazVQl","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","messageID":"msg_f1c2e54d40016ostd7nghcJ7Z6","sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":61730,"input":812,"output":431,"reasoning":71,"cache":{"write":0,"read":60416}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782884248398,"sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","part":{"id":"prt_f1c2eab4d001CJJ4pyIqqLs3ZS","messageID":"msg_f1c2ea693001K0etL3sKm2vKeV","sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782884273594,"sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5Xm99DDd6l6Nz2SBDWvzpZfC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/spec.md","offset":55,"limit":75},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n55: \n56: ### Problem Statement\n57: Our loop-based systems (deep-loop-runtime, deep-loop-workflows, and the system-spec-kit commands/agents that drive them) carry known gaps in resilience, convergence quality, observability, safety, and interconnection. We need a disciplined way to discover concrete, evidence-backed improvements and then apply them without losing track of dependencies.\n58: \n59: ### Purpose\n60: This packet first researches two vendored reference codebases for portable patterns (phase `001-reference-research`), then applies the resulting loop-system improvements as independently-executable phases (`002`-`007`, by subsystem). Phase `008` remediates deep-review follow-ups.\n61: \n62: > **Phase-parent note:** This spec.md is the ONLY authored document at the parent level. All detailed planning, task breakdowns, checklists, and decisions live in the child phase folders listed in the Phase Documentation Map below.\n63: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n68: ## 3. SCOPE\n69: \n70: ### In Scope\n71: - Reference research mining loop-cli-main + kasper into a ranked recommendation backlog (`001-reference-research`).\n72: - Phased implementation of the 40 loop-system recommendations as top-level phases `002`-`007` (by subsystem), followed by remediation in `008`.\n73: \n74: ### Out of Scope\n75: - Subsystems unrelated to loop orchestration.\n76: - Implementing improvements at the parent level — all work is delegated to child phases.\n77: \n78: ### Files to Change\n79: Audit-trail summary only; per-phase detail lives in each child's plan.md.\n80: \n81: | File Path | Change Type | Phase | Description |\n82: |-----------|-------------|-------|-------------|\n83: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/**` | Modify | 002-deep-loop-runtime | Resilience, convergence, observability improvements |\n84: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/**` | Modify | 003-deep-loop-workflows | Anti-convergence, injection, interconnection improvements |\n85: | `.opencode/commands/{deep,speckit}/**` | Modify | 004-006 | Telemetry, run-now, autopilot improvements |\n86: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: <!-- ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n91: ## PHASE DOCUMENTATION MAP\n92: \n93: > This spec uses phased decomposition. Each phase is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details (plan, tasks, checklist, decisions, continuity) live inside the phase children.\n94: \n95: | Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n96: |-------|--------|-------|--------|\n97: | 001 | `001-reference-research` | 50-iteration mining of loop-cli-main + kasper → 40 recommendations | Complete |\n98: | 002 | `002-deep-loop-runtime` | 18 runtime recs: atomic-state, loop-lock, sleep, jsonl, executor/fallback, coverage-graph, fanout, lifecycle | Complete |\n99: | 003 | `003-deep-loop-workflows` | 12 workflow recs: anti-convergence + ADRs, injection-inbox, ideas/rejected caches, benchmark, push-wave | Complete |\n100: | 004 | `004-system-spec-kit` | Speckit autopilot lifecycle | Complete |\n101: | 005 | `005-skill-interconnection` | Advisor routing projection | Complete |\n102: | 006 | `006-ux-observability-automation` | Dashboards, telemetry heartbeat, run-now, dry-run, observability envelope, memory-upsert | Complete |\n103: | 007 | `007-testing` | Hermetic test isolation, record-replay cassette harness | Complete |\n104: | 008 | `008-loop-systems-remediation` | Remediate deep-review deferred findings + MiMo-campaign recs (rollback hash-guard, promotion safety, benchmark ledger, adversarial playbook scenarios, tightened pass-criteria, test-adequacy) | In Progress |\n105: \n106: ### Phase Transition Rules\n107: \n108: - Each phase MUST pass `validate.sh` independently before the next phase begins\n109: - Parent spec tracks aggregate progress via this map\n110: - Use `/speckit:resume [parent-folder]/[NNN-phase]/` to resume a specific phase\n111: - Run `validate.sh --recursive` on parent to validate all phases as integrated unit\n112: \n113: ### Phase Handoff Criteria\n114: \n115: | From | To | Criteria | Verification |\n116: |------|-----|----------|--------------|\n117: | 001 | 002 | Ranked recommendation backlog synthesized | `001-reference-research/research/research.md` present |\n118: | 007 | 008 | Implementation phases shipped + deep-reviewed; remediation backlog triaged | `review/review-report.md` + `review/mimo-campaign-report.md` present |\n119: <!-- /ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n124: ## 4. OPEN QUESTIONS\n125: \n126: - Cross-subsystem convergence dependencies (the convergence-profile ADR must precede new convergence signals) are tracked via per-phase `Predecessor` fields rather than folder order.\n127: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n128: \n129: ---\n\n(Showing lines 55-129 of 135. Use offset=130 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n### Problem Statement\nOur loop-based systems (deep-loop-runtime, deep-loop-workflows, and the system-spec-kit commands/agents that drive them) carry known gaps in resilience, convergence quality, observability, safety, and interconnection. We need a disciplined way to discover concrete, evidence-backed improvements and then apply them without losing track of dependencies.\n\n### Purpose\nThis packet first researches two vendored reference codebases for portable patterns (phase `001-reference-research`), then applies the resulting loop-system improvements as independently-executable phases (`002`-`007`, by subsystem). Phase `008` remediates deep-review follow-ups.\n\n> **Phase-parent note:** This spec.md is the ONLY authored document at the parent level. All detailed planning, task breakdowns, checklists, and decisions live in the child phase folders listed in the Phase Documentation Map below.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Reference research mining loop-cli-main + kasper into a ranked recommendation backlog (`001-reference-research`).\n- Phased implementation of the 40 loop-system recommendations as top-level phases `002`-`007` (by subsystem), followed by remediation in `008`.\n\n### Out of Scope","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/spec.md","text":"\n### Problem Statement\nOur loop-based systems (deep-loop-runtime, deep-loop-workflows, and the system-spec-kit commands/agents that drive them) carry known gaps in resilience, convergence quality, observability, safety, and interconnection. We need a disciplined way to discover concrete, evidence-backed improvements and then apply them without losing track of dependencies.\n\n### Purpose\nThis packet first researches two vendored reference codebases for portable patterns (phase `001-reference-research`), then applies the resulting loop-system improvements as independently-executable phases (`002`-`007`, by subsystem). Phase `008` remediates deep-review follow-ups.\n\n> **Phase-parent note:** This spec.md is the ONLY authored document at the parent level. All detailed planning, task breakdowns, checklists, and decisions live in the child phase folders listed in the Phase Documentation Map below.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Reference research mining loop-cli-main + kasper into a ranked recommendation backlog (`001-reference-research`).\n- Phased implementation of the 40 loop-system recommendations as top-level phases `002`-`007` (by subsystem), followed by remediation in `008`.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Subsystems unrelated to loop orchestration.\n- Implementing improvements at the parent level — all work is delegated to child phases.\n\n### Files to Change\nAudit-trail summary only; per-phase detail lives in each child's plan.md.\n\n| File Path | Change Type | Phase | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|-------|-------------|\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/**` | Modify | 002-deep-loop-runtime | Resilience, convergence, observability improvements |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/**` | Modify | 003-deep-loop-workflows | Anti-convergence, injection, interconnection improvements |\n| `.opencode/commands/{deep,speckit}/**` | Modify | 004-006 | Telemetry, run-now, autopilot improvements |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n## PHASE DOCUMENTATION MAP\n\n> This spec uses phased decomposition. Each phase is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details (plan, tasks, checklist, decisions, continuity) live inside the phase children.\n\n| Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n|-------|--------|-------|--------|\n| 001 | `001-reference-research` | 50-iteration mining of loop-cli-main + kasper → 40 recommendations | Complete |\n| 002 | `002-deep-loop-runtime` | 18 runtime recs: atomic-state, loop-lock, sleep, jsonl, executor/fallback, coverage-graph, fanout, lifecycle | Complete |\n| 003 | `003-deep-loop-workflows` | 12 workflow recs: anti-convergence + ADRs, injection-inbox, ideas/rejected caches, benchmark, push-wave | Complete |\n| 004 | `004-system-spec-kit` | Speckit autopilot lifecycle | Complete |\n| 005 | `005-skill-interconnection` | Advisor routing projection | Complete |\n| 006 | `006-ux-observability-automation` | Dashboards, telemetry heartbeat, run-now, dry-run, observability envelope, memory-upsert | Complete |\n| 007 | `007-testing` | Hermetic test isolation, record-replay cassette harness | Complete |\n| 008 | `008-loop-systems-remediation` | Remediate deep-review deferred findings + MiMo-campaign recs (rollback hash-guard, promotion safety, benchmark ledger, adversarial playbook scenarios, tightened pass-criteria, test-adequacy) | In Progress |\n\n### Phase Transition Rules\n\n- Each phase MUST pass `validate.sh` independently before the next phase begins\n- Parent spec tracks aggregate progress via this map\n- Use `/speckit:resume [parent-folder]/[NNN-phase]/` to resume a specific phase\n- Run `validate.sh --recursive` on parent to validate all phases as integrated unit\n\n### Phase Handoff Criteria\n\n| From | To | Criteria | Verification |\n|------|-----|----------|--------------|\n| 001 | 002 | Ranked recommendation backlog synthesized | `001-reference-research/research/research.md` present |\n| 007 | 008 | Implementation phases shipped + deep-reviewed; remediation backlog triaged | `review/review-report.md` + `review/mimo-campaign-report.md` present |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 4. OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- Cross-subsystem convergence dependencies (the convergence-profile ADR must precede new convergence signals) are tracked via per-phase `Predecessor` fields rather than folder order.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n\n---","lineStart":55,"lineEnd":129,"totalLines":135,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/spec.md","time":{"start":1782884273591,"end":1782884273593}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0505af6371f3f063016a44a7b184c48191935921132212fbcc"}},"id":"prt_f1c2f0d900013BPRcdIONVxzZw","sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","messageID":"msg_f1c2ea693001K0etL3sKm2vKeV"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782884273629,"sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vcHoOZGxsIRWXkaJfrjT6paN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/002-deep-loop-runtime/spec.md","offset":70,"limit":75},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/002-deep-loop-runtime/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n70: ### Problem Statement\n71: The deep-loop-runtime core library and scripts carry known structural gaps across four dimensions: (1) **resilience** — atomic state writes are unguarded for integrity and redundancy, the loop lock has no heartbeat during long dispatch, and there is no crash-resume for killed wait-boundary processes; (2) **convergence quality** — the convergence signal has no improvement-effect delta, no observation-threshold guard, and no time-decay on stale evidence; (3) **observability** — log transcript navigation requires full-file scanning and there is no byte-offset indexing; (4) **robustness** — the fallback router retries blindly by failure type, the fan-out pool has no stall watchdog, and the LLM judge path has no hardening against model call failures.\n72: \n73: ### Purpose\n74: Implement all 18 evidence-backed improvements mined from the reference codebases (`loop-cli-main`, `kasper`) in dependency order, so that deep-loop-runtime emerges with durable atomic state, a live heartbeat lock, convergence signals that detect \"looping without improving\", and robust failure-routing throughout the runtime.\n75: \n76: > **Phase-parent note:** This spec.md is the ONLY authored document at this subsystem level. All detailed planning, task breakdowns, checklists, and decisions live in the 18 child leaf folders listed in the Phase Documentation Map below.\n77: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n82: ## 3. SCOPE\n83: \n84: ### In Scope\n85: - All 18 improvement items from research.md §5.1 (deep-loop-runtime subsection), implemented as independently-executable leaf phases\n86: - Changes are limited to files under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/` and `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/` that are explicitly called out per leaf\n87: - Each leaf is self-contained: it modifies only the files listed in its own Files to Change table\n88: \n89: ### Out of Scope\n90: - Improvements targeting `deep-loop-workflows`, `system-spec-kit`, or `skill-interconnection` subsystems (other subsystem groups in `123-agent-loops-improved`)\n91: - The \"deep variant\" parts explicitly called out per leaf (LLM consolidation, multi-hop fallback chains, no-backlog catch-up, full JSONL end-to-end integrity, socket-bind as default, 4-stage JSON extraction cascade) — these are deferred to follow-on specs\n92: - Any new capability outside the 18 research.md §5.1 items\n93: \n94: ### Files to Change\n95: Audit-trail summary only; per-leaf detail lives in each child's Files to Change table.\n96: \n97: | File Path | Change Type | Leaf(s) | Description |\n98: |-----------|-------------|---------|-------------|\n99: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts` | Modify | 001, 002, 003 | Serialize-diff, SHA-256 integrity, deferred writer |\n100: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/sleep.ts` | Create | 004 | Abortable chunked sleep primitive |\n101: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/lifecycle-taxonomy.cjs` | Modify | 005 | State-machine taxonomy + transition guards |\n102: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts` | Modify | 006 | Lock-held read-merge-write set-union |\n103: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/loop-lock.ts` | Modify | 007, 008 | Heartbeat hardening + optional socket-bind ADR |\n104: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts` | Modify | 009, 016 | Byte-offset log regions + LLM-judge hardening |\n105: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | Modify | 010, 018 | Fixed-rate accounting + persisted-wait crash-resume |\n106: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` | Modify | 011, 012 | Score-delta + observation-threshold guard |\n107: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts` | Modify | 013 | Time-decay weighting |\n108: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-query.ts` | Modify | 014 | Fuzzy finding-merge |\n109: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Modify | 015 | Typed outcome-routed reroute |\n110: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | Modify | 017 | Stall-watchdog abort/requeue |\n111: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` | Modify | 009, 010, 018 | Byte-offset, overrun accounting, crash-resume hooks |\n112: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: <!-- ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n117: ## PHASE DOCUMENTATION MAP\n118: \n119: > This spec uses phased decomposition. Each leaf is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details (plan, tasks, checklist, decisions, continuity) live inside the leaf children. Recommended implementation order follows the dependency chain from research.md §6: atomic-state + integrity first → heartbeat + sleep → convergence signals → fallback/coverage → deep-rewrites last.\n120: \n121: | Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n122: |-------|--------|-------|--------|\n123: | 001 | `001-atomic-state-serialize-diff/` | Write-only-on-change diff guard for `atomic-state.ts` | Draft |\n124: | 002 | `002-atomic-state-integrity-helpers/` | SHA-256 stamp/verify helpers for `atomic-state.ts` | Draft |\n125: | 003 | `003-atomic-state-deferred-writer/` | Debounced per-path coalescing writer for `atomic-state.ts` | Draft |\n126: | 004 | `004-abortable-chunked-sleep/` | New cancellation-safe `sleep.ts` primitive | Draft |\n127: | 005 | `005-lifecycle-taxonomy-guards/` | State-machine taxonomy + legal transition table in `lifecycle-taxonomy.cjs` | Draft |\n128: | 006 | `006-jsonl-lock-held-merge/` | Lock-held read-merge-write set-union in `jsonl-repair.ts` | Draft |\n129: | 007 | `007-loop-lock-heartbeat-hardening/` | Owner-scoped heartbeat driver + pause-aware metadata in `loop-lock.ts` | Draft |\n130: | 008 | `008-loop-lock-single-flight-decision/` | ADR: optional socket-bind single-flight guard for `loop-lock.ts` | Draft |\n131: | 009 | `009-byte-offset-log-regions/` | Optional `logOffset`/`logSize`/`logPath` fields per iteration record | Draft |\n132: | 010 | `010-fixed-rate-overrun-accounting/` | Slot overrun measurement + `skippedCount` metadata in `fanout-run.cjs` | Draft |\n133: | 011 | `011-convergence-score-delta/` | `scoreDelta` improvement-effect signal in `convergence.cjs` | Draft |\n134: | 012 | `012-observation-threshold-guard/` | `min_observations` actionability guard in `convergence.cjs` | Draft |\n135: | 013 | `013-coverage-graph-time-decay/` | Time-decay weighting in `coverage-graph-signals.ts` | Draft |\n136: | 014 | `014-coverage-graph-fuzzy-merge/` | Deterministic fuzzy node-merge in `coverage-graph-query.ts` | Draft |\n137: | 015 | `015-fallback-router-typed-reroute/` | Typed `failureKind` routing + `validateFallbackGraph()` preflight | Draft |\n138: | 016 | `016-llm-judge-hardening/` | Retry + neutral fallback card + timeout races in `post-dispatch-validate.ts` | Draft |\n139: | 017 | `017-fanout-stall-watchdog/` | Opt-in stall watchdog abort/requeue in `fanout-pool.cjs` | Draft |\n140: | 018 | `018-persisted-wait-crash-resume/` | Nullable wait-checkpoint schema + `resume-waiting` classifier in `fanout-run.cjs` | Draft |\n141: \n142: ### Phase Transition Rules\n143: \n144: - Each leaf MUST pass `validate.sh --strict` independently before the next leaf begins\n\n(Showing lines 70-144 of 191. Use offset=145 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"### Problem Statement\nThe deep-loop-runtime core library and scripts carry known structural gaps across four dimensions: (1) **resilience** — atomic state writes are unguarded for integrity and redundancy, the loop lock has no heartbeat during long dispatch, and there is no crash-resume for killed wait-boundary processes; (2) **convergence quality** — the convergence signal has no improvement-effect delta, no observation-threshold guard, and no time-decay on stale evidence; (3) **observability** — log transcript navigation requires full-file scanning and there is no byte-offset indexing; (4) **robustness** — the fallback router retries blindly by failure type, the fan-out pool has no stall watchdog, and the LLM judge path has no hardening against model call failures.\n\n### Purpose\nImplement all 18 evidence-backed improvements mined from the reference codebases (`loop-cli-main`, `kasper`) in dependency order, so that deep-loop-runtime emerges with durable atomic state, a live heartbeat lock, convergence signals that detect \"looping without improving\", and robust failure-routing throughout the runtime.\n\n> **Phase-parent note:** This spec.md is the ONLY authored document at this subsystem level. All detailed planning, task breakdowns, checklists, and decisions live in the 18 child leaf folders listed in the Phase Documentation Map below.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- All 18 improvement items from research.md §5.1 (deep-loop-runtime subsection), implemented as independently-executable leaf phases\n- Changes are limited to files under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/` and `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/` that are explicitly called out per leaf\n- Each leaf is self-contained: it modifies only the files listed in its own Files to Change table\n\n### Out of Scope","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/002-deep-loop-runtime/spec.md","text":"### Problem Statement\nThe deep-loop-runtime core library and scripts carry known structural gaps across four dimensions: (1) **resilience** — atomic state writes are unguarded for integrity and redundancy, the loop lock has no heartbeat during long dispatch, and there is no crash-resume for killed wait-boundary processes; (2) **convergence quality** — the convergence signal has no improvement-effect delta, no observation-threshold guard, and no time-decay on stale evidence; (3) **observability** — log transcript navigation requires full-file scanning and there is no byte-offset indexing; (4) **robustness** — the fallback router retries blindly by failure type, the fan-out pool has no stall watchdog, and the LLM judge path has no hardening against model call failures.\n\n### Purpose\nImplement all 18 evidence-backed improvements mined from the reference codebases (`loop-cli-main`, `kasper`) in dependency order, so that deep-loop-runtime emerges with durable atomic state, a live heartbeat lock, convergence signals that detect \"looping without improving\", and robust failure-routing throughout the runtime.\n\n> **Phase-parent note:** This spec.md is the ONLY authored document at this subsystem level. All detailed planning, task breakdowns, checklists, and decisions live in the 18 child leaf folders listed in the Phase Documentation Map below.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- All 18 improvement items from research.md §5.1 (deep-loop-runtime subsection), implemented as independently-executable leaf phases\n- Changes are limited to files under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/` and `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/` that are explicitly called out per leaf\n- Each leaf is self-contained: it modifies only the files listed in its own Files to Change table\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Improvements targeting `deep-loop-workflows`, `system-spec-kit`, or `skill-interconnection` subsystems (other subsystem groups in `123-agent-loops-improved`)\n- The \"deep variant\" parts explicitly called out per leaf (LLM consolidation, multi-hop fallback chains, no-backlog catch-up, full JSONL end-to-end integrity, socket-bind as default, 4-stage JSON extraction cascade) — these are deferred to follow-on specs\n- Any new capability outside the 18 research.md §5.1 items\n\n### Files to Change\nAudit-trail summary only; per-leaf detail lives in each child's Files to Change table.\n\n| File Path | Change Type | Leaf(s) | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|---------|-------------|\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts` | Modify | 001, 002, 003 | Serialize-diff, SHA-256 integrity, deferred writer |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/sleep.ts` | Create | 004 | Abortable chunked sleep primitive |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/lifecycle-taxonomy.cjs` | Modify | 005 | State-machine taxonomy + transition guards |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts` | Modify | 006 | Lock-held read-merge-write set-union |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/loop-lock.ts` | Modify | 007, 008 | Heartbeat hardening + optional socket-bind ADR |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts` | Modify | 009, 016 | Byte-offset log regions + LLM-judge hardening |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | Modify | 010, 018 | Fixed-rate accounting + persisted-wait crash-resume |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` | Modify | 011, 012 | Score-delta + observation-threshold guard |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts` | Modify | 013 | Time-decay weighting |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-query.ts` | Modify | 014 | Fuzzy finding-merge |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Modify | 015 | Typed outcome-routed reroute |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | Modify | 017 | Stall-watchdog abort/requeue |\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` | Modify | 009, 010, 018 | Byte-offset, overrun accounting, crash-resume hooks |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n## PHASE DOCUMENTATION MAP\n\n> This spec uses phased decomposition. Each leaf is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details (plan, tasks, checklist, decisions, continuity) live inside the leaf children. Recommended implementation order follows the dependency chain from research.md §6: atomic-state + integrity first → heartbeat + sleep → convergence signals → fallback/coverage → deep-rewrites last.\n\n| Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n|-------|--------|-------|--------|\n| 001 | `001-atomic-state-serialize-diff/` | Write-only-on-change diff guard for `atomic-state.ts` | Draft |\n| 002 | `002-atomic-state-integrity-helpers/` | SHA-256 stamp/verify helpers for `atomic-state.ts` | Draft |\n| 003 | `003-atomic-state-deferred-writer/` | Debounced per-path coalescing writer for `atomic-state.ts` | Draft |\n| 004 | `004-abortable-chunked-sleep/` | New cancellation-safe `sleep.ts` primitive | Draft |\n| 005 | `005-lifecycle-taxonomy-guards/` | State-machine taxonomy + legal transition table in `lifecycle-taxonomy.cjs` | Draft |\n| 006 | `006-jsonl-lock-held-merge/` | Lock-held read-merge-write set-union in `jsonl-repair.ts` | Draft |\n| 007 | `007-loop-lock-heartbeat-hardening/` | Owner-scoped heartbeat driver + pause-aware metadata in `loop-lock.ts` | Draft |\n| 008 | `008-loop-lock-single-flight-decision/` | ADR: optional socket-bind single-flight guard for `loop-lock.ts` | Draft |\n| 009 | `009-byte-offset-log-regions/` | Optional `logOffset`/`logSize`/`logPath` fields per iteration record | Draft |\n| 010 | `010-fixed-rate-overrun-accounting/` | Slot overrun measurement + `skippedCount` metadata in `fanout-run.cjs` | Draft |\n| 011 | `011-convergence-score-delta/` | `scoreDelta` improvement-effect signal in `convergence.cjs` | Draft |\n| 012 | `012-observation-threshold-guard/` | `min_observations` actionability guard in `convergence.cjs` | Draft |\n| 013 | `013-coverage-graph-time-decay/` | Time-decay weighting in `coverage-graph-signals.ts` | Draft |\n| 014 | `014-coverage-graph-fuzzy-merge/` | Deterministic fuzzy node-merge in `coverage-graph-query.ts` | Draft |\n| 015 | `015-fallback-router-typed-reroute/` | Typed `failureKind` routing + `validateFallbackGraph()` preflight | Draft |\n| 016 | `016-llm-judge-hardening/` | Retry + neutral fallback card + timeout races in `post-dispatch-validate.ts` | Draft |\n| 017 | `017-fanout-stall-watchdog/` | Opt-in stall watchdog abort/requeue in `fanout-pool.cjs` | Draft |\n| 018 | `018-persisted-wait-crash-resume/` | Nullable wait-checkpoint schema + `resume-waiting` classifier in `fanout-run.cjs` | Draft |\n\n### Phase Transition Rules\n\n- Each leaf MUST pass `validate.sh --strict` independently before the next leaf begins","lineStart":70,"lineEnd":144,"totalLines":191,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/002-deep-loop-runtime/spec.md","time":{"start":1782884273625,"end":1782884273628}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0505af6371f3f063016a44a7b184d88191a9692ed1c167e6eb"}},"id":"prt_f1c2f0dc5001MmAQI6C92p5t64","sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","messageID":"msg_f1c2ea693001K0etL3sKm2vKeV"}}
