h` independently before the next phase begins\n221: - Parent spec tracks aggregate progress via this map\n222: - Use `/speckit:resume [parent-folder]/[NNN-phase]/` to resume a specific phase\n223: - Run `validate.sh --recursive` on parent to validate all phases as integrated unit\n224: \n225: ### Phase Handoff Criteria\n226: \n227: | From | To | Criteria | Verification |\n228: |------|-----|----------|--------------|\n229: | 001-dashboard-sparkline-trend | 002-single-loop-telemetry-heartbeat | Sparkline renders in reduce-state.cjs without errors | Manual run of reduce-state shows `## 5. TREND` block |\n230: | 002-single-loop-telemetry-heartbeat | 003-unified-observability-event-envelope | Single-loop rows parse like fan-out rows | Parity test passes |\n231: | 003-unified-observability-event-envelope | 004-run-now-control | Envelope module exports `normalizeObservabilityEvent` | TypeScript import resolves |\n232: | 004-run-now-control | 005-per-iteration-memory-upsert | Sentinel consumed-once behavior verified | JSONL events emitted correctly |\n233: | 005-per-iteration-memory-upsert | 006-loop-wide-dry-run | Memory upsert step runs non-fatally | No error thrown on MCP unavailability |\n234: <!-- /ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n\n(End of file - total 234 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## PHASE DOCUMENTATION MAP\n\n> This spec uses phased decomposition. Each phase is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details (plan, tasks, checklist, decisions, continuity) live inside the phase children.\n\n| Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n|-------|--------|-------|--------|\n| 1 | `001-dashboard-sparkline-trend/` | Pure reducer change: `renderSparkline()` for newInfoRatio/score history in `## 5. TREND` terminal gate | Draft |\n| 2 | `002-single-loop-telemetry-heartbeat/` | `started`/`progress`/terminal rows with `label:\"single\"` in deep_research_auto.yaml; parity with fan-out dashboard | Draft |\n| 3 | `003-unified-observability-event-envelope/` | New `observability-events.cjs` with `normalizeObservabilityEvent()` / `appendObservabilityEvent()`; additive | Draft |\n| 4 | `004-run-now-control/` | `.deep-research-run-now` sentinel: consume-once, pause precedence, JSONL lifecycle events | Draft |\n| 5 | `005-per-iteration-memory-upsert/` | `step_memory_upsert_iteration` after validate/reduce/graph-upsert; non-fatal `memory_save` call | Draft |\n| 6 | `006-loop-wide-dry-run/` | `--dry-run` as first-class input; halt at every mutation boundary with no dispatch/state mutation | Draft |\n\n### Phase Transition Rules\n\n- Each phase MUST pass `validate.sh` independently before the next phase begins\n- Parent spec tracks aggregate progress via this map\n- Use `/speckit:resume [parent-folder]/[NNN-phase]/` to resume a specific phase\n- Run `validate.sh --recursive` on parent to validate all phases as integrated unit\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/006-ux-observability-automation/spec.md","text":"## PHASE DOCUMENTATION MAP\n\n> This spec uses phased decomposition. Each phase is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details (plan, tasks, checklist, decisions, continuity) live inside the phase children.\n\n| Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n|-------|--------|-------|--------|\n| 1 | `001-dashboard-sparkline-trend/` | Pure reducer change: `renderSparkline()` for newInfoRatio/score history in `## 5. TREND` terminal gate | Draft |\n| 2 | `002-single-loop-telemetry-heartbeat/` | `started`/`progress`/terminal rows with `label:\"single\"` in deep_research_auto.yaml; parity with fan-out dashboard | Draft |\n| 3 | `003-unified-observability-event-envelope/` | New `observability-events.cjs` with `normalizeObservabilityEvent()` / `appendObservabilityEvent()`; additive | Draft |\n| 4 | `004-run-now-control/` | `.deep-research-run-now` sentinel: consume-once, pause precedence, JSONL lifecycle events | Draft |\n| 5 | `005-per-iteration-memory-upsert/` | `step_memory_upsert_iteration` after validate/reduce/graph-upsert; non-fatal `memory_save` call | Draft |\n| 6 | `006-loop-wide-dry-run/` | `--dry-run` as first-class input; halt at every mutation boundary with no dispatch/state mutation | Draft |\n\n### Phase Transition Rules\n\n- Each phase MUST pass `validate.sh` independently before the next phase begins\n- Parent spec tracks aggregate progress via this map\n- Use `/speckit:resume [parent-folder]/[NNN-phase]/` to resume a specific phase\n- Run `validate.sh --recursive` on parent to validate all phases as integrated unit\n\n### Phase Handoff Criteria\n\n| From | To | Criteria | Verification |\n|------|-----|----------|--------------|\n| 001-dashboard-sparkline-trend | 002-single-loop-telemetry-heartbeat | Sparkline renders in reduce-state.cjs without errors | Manual run of reduce-state shows `## 5. TREND` block |\n| 002-single-loop-telemetry-heartbeat | 003-unified-observability-event-envelope | Single-loop rows parse like fan-out rows | Parity test passes |\n| 003-unified-observability-event-envelope | 004-run-now-control | Envelope module exports `normalizeObservabilityEvent` | TypeScript import resolves |\n| 004-run-now-control | 005-per-iteration-memory-upsert | Sentinel consumed-once behavior verified | JSONL events emitted correctly |\n| 005-per-iteration-memory-upsert | 006-loop-wide-dry-run | Memory upsert step runs non-fatally | No error thrown on MCP unavailability |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-map -->","lineStart":205,"lineEnd":234,"totalLines":234,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/006-ux-observability-automation/spec.md","time":{"start":1782884273739,"end":1782884273746}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0505af6371f3f063016a44a7b184f48191bb3bb27b74fb3e8a"}},"id":"prt_f1c2f0e4b001V71joQXUbuinOQ","sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","messageID":"msg_f1c