{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782884281140,"sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kHdRdmlAJUte4ZsFwywkaN5P","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/spec.md","offset":100,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n100: \n101: > This spec uses phased decomposition. Each phase is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details (plan, tasks, checklist, decisions, continuity) live inside the phase children.\n102: \n103: | Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n104: |-------|--------|-------|--------|\n105: | 001 | `001-anti-convergence-floor/` | `minIterations` + `convergenceMode:\"off\"` guard in research config and YAML | Draft |\n106: | 002 | `002-convergence-profile-unification-adr/` | ADR freezing shared convergence profile shape + parity test | Draft |\n107: | 003 | `003-cross-mode-anti-convergence-adr/` | `antiConvergence` contract projected across all four mode configs + optimizer invariant group | Draft |\n108: | 004 | `004-injection-inbox-provenance/` | `research/inbox.jsonl` canonical injection surface with durable provenance records | Draft |\n109: | 005 | `005-anchor-ownership-conflict-adr/` | `resolveQuestionConflicts()` + `question_conflict` event; `key-questions` as generated projection | Draft |\n110: | 006 | `006-rejected-pattern-cache/` | Bounded `ideaRejected` event index with exact + fuzzy check before candidates | Draft |\n111: | 007 | `007-ideas-backlog-lifecycle/` | Three-part idea lifecycle: `idea_observed` → `idea_promoted` → `idea_rejected` with reducer ownership | Draft |\n112: | 008 | `008-code-graph-coverage-bridge/` | Code-graph → coverage-graph seeding before first convergence check; `seed_source`/`seed_confidence` | Draft |\n113: | 009 | `009-loop-quality-benchmark/` | `outcomeScoreDelta` + `fixtureDeltas[]` in benchmark; promotion gate on improvement-over-baseline | Draft |\n114: | 010 | `010-deep-improvement-accepted-vs-shipped/` | Split accept (preserve) from ship (merge); `promotion_blocked_branch_preserved`; `rollback-candidate.cjs` | Draft |\n115: | 011 | `011-meta-loop-lane-d-packaging/` | Lane D packaging profile for `deep-loop-runtime` + `--self-target` guard | Draft |\n116: | 012 | `012-push-wave-fanout/` | `depends_on`/`touches` schema + `flat_pool` guard; wave planner interface stub (not activated) | Draft |\n117: \n118: ### Phase Transition Rules\n119: \n120: - Each phase MUST pass `validate.sh` independently before the next phase begins\n121: - Parent spec tracks aggregate progress via this map\n122: - Use `/speckit:resume [parent-folder]/[NNN-phase]/` to resume a specific phase\n123: - Run `validate.sh --recursive` on parent to validate all phases as an integrated unit\n124: \n125: ### Phase Handoff Criteria\n126: \n127: | From | To | Criteria | Verification |\n128: |------|-----|----------|--------------|\n129: | 001 | 002 | `minIterations` guard in config and YAML; `min_iterations_guard_pass` event present | validate.sh on 001 |\n130: | 002 | 003 | ADR document present; parity test green on current code | validate.sh on 002 |\n131: | 003 | 004 | All four mode configs have `antiConvergence` block; optimizer invariant group rejects violations | validate.sh on 003 |\n132: | 004 | 005 | `research/inbox.jsonl` schema frozen; reducer reads inbox with `origin` propagation | validate.sh on 004 |\n133: | 005 | 006 | `resolveQuestionConflicts()` implemented; `question_conflict` event emitted on disagreement | validate.sh on 005 |\n134: | 006 | 007 | Bounded rejected index in place; exact + fuzzy check before candidates | validate.sh on 006 |\n135: | 007 | 008 | Three-part idea lifecycle events in JSONL; reducer owns promotion | validate.sh on 007 |\n136: | 008 | 009 | Coverage graph seeded before first convergence check; seeded nodes carry metadata | validate.sh on 008 |\n137: | 009 | 010 | `outcomeScoreDelta` gate in promotion; helped/hurt in benchmark report | validate.sh on 009 |\n138: | 010 | 011 | Two-phase promotion; `rollback-candidate.cjs` present | validate.sh on 010 |\n139: | 011 | 012 | `deep-loop-runtime.json` profile validates; `--self-target` guard in command | validate.sh on 011 |\n140: <!-- /ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n145: ## 4. OPEN QUESTIONS\n146: \n147: - The convergence-profile unification ADR (002) must precede the cross-mode contract (003) in ratification order; if 002 takes longer than expected, can 003 proceed with a provisional profile shape?\n148: - The push-wave fan-out (012) is dependency-last; if the conflict-safety substrate is not delivered by other teams in time, should 012's schema+guard deliverables still ship to unblock future activation?\n149: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n154: \n155: - **Phase children**: See `[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/` sub-folders for per-phase spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n156: - **Source research**: `../../../001-reference-research/research/research.md` §5.2\n157: - **Parent Spec**: `../../spec.md` (123-agent-loops-improved)\n158: - **Graph Metadata**: See `graph-metadata.json` for `derived.last_active_child_id` pointer\n159: \n160: <!-- SCAFFOLD_VALIDATION_COUNTS:\n161: REQ-003\n162: REQ-004\n163: REQ-005\n164: REQ-006\n165: REQ-007\n166: REQ-008\n167: **Given**\n168: **Given**\n169: **Given**\n170: **Given**\n171: **Given**\n172: **Given**\n173: -->\n\n(End of file - total 173 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n> This spec uses phased decomposition. Each phase is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details (plan, tasks, checklist, decisions, continuity) live inside the phase children.\n\n| Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n|-------|--------|-------|--------|\n| 001 | `001-anti-convergence-floor/` | `minIterations` + `convergenceMode:\"off\"` guard in research config and YAML | Draft |\n| 002 | `002-convergence-profile-unification-adr/` | ADR freezing shared convergence profile shape + parity test | Draft |\n| 003 | `003-cross-mode-anti-convergence-adr/` | `antiConvergence` contract projected across all four mode configs + optimizer invariant group | Draft |\n| 004 | `004-injection-inbox-provenance/` | `research/inbox.jsonl` canonical injection surface with durable provenance records | Draft |\n| 005 | `005-anchor-ownership-conflict-adr/` | `resolveQuestionConflicts()` + `question_conflict` event; `key-questions` as generated projection | Draft |\n| 006 | `006-rejected-pattern-cache/` | Bounded `ideaRejected` event index with exact + fuzzy check before candidates | Draft |\n| 007 | `007-ideas-backlog-lifecycle/` | Three-part idea lifecycle: `idea_observed` → `idea_promoted` → `idea_rejected` with reducer ownership | Draft |\n| 008 | `008-code-graph-coverage-bridge/` | Code-graph → coverage-graph seeding before first convergence check; `seed_source`/`seed_confidence` | Draft |\n| 009 | `009-loop-quality-benchmark/` | `outcomeScoreDelta` + `fixtureDeltas[]` in benchmark; promotion gate on improvement-over-baseline | Draft |\n| 010 | `010-deep-improvement-accepted-vs-shipped/` | Split accept (preserve) from ship (merge); `promotion_blocked_branch_preserved`; `rollback-candidate.cjs` | Draft |\n| 011 | `011-meta-loop-lane-d-packaging/` | Lane D packaging profile for `deep-loop-runtime` + `--self-target` guard | Draft |\n| 012 | `012-push-wave-fanout/` | `depends_on`/`touches` schema + `flat_pool` guard; wave planner interface stub (not activated) | Draft |\n\n### Phase Transition Rules\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/spec.md","text":"\n> This spec uses phased decomposition. Each phase is an independently executable child spec folder. All implementation details (plan, tasks, checklist, decisions, continuity) live inside the phase children.\n\n| Phase | Folder | Focus | Status |\n|-------|--------|-------|--------|\n| 001 | `001-anti-convergence-floor/` | `minIterations` + `convergenceMode:\"off\"` guard in research config and YAML | Draft |\n| 002 | `002-convergence-profile-unification-adr/` | ADR freezing shared convergence profile shape + parity test | Draft |\n| 003 | `003-cross-mode-anti-convergence-adr/` | `antiConvergence` contract projected across all four mode configs + optimizer invariant group | Draft |\n| 004 | `004-injection-inbox-provenance/` | `research/inbox.jsonl` canonical injection surface with durable provenance records | Draft |\n| 005 | `005-anchor-ownership-conflict-adr/` | `resolveQuestionConflicts()` + `question_conflict` event; `key-questions` as generated projection | Draft |\n| 006 | `006-rejected-pattern-cache/` | Bounded `ideaRejected` event index with exact + fuzzy check before candidates | Draft |\n| 007 | `007-ideas-backlog-lifecycle/` | Three-part idea lifecycle: `idea_observed` → `idea_promoted` → `idea_rejected` with reducer ownership | Draft |\n| 008 | `008-code-graph-coverage-bridge/` | Code-graph → coverage-graph seeding before first convergence check; `seed_source`/`seed_confidence` | Draft |\n| 009 | `009-loop-quality-benchmark/` | `outcomeScoreDelta` + `fixtureDeltas[]` in benchmark; promotion gate on improvement-over-baseline | Draft |\n| 010 | `010-deep-improvement-accepted-vs-shipped/` | Split accept (preserve) from ship (merge); `promotion_blocked_branch_preserved`; `rollback-candidate.cjs` | Draft |\n| 011 | `011-meta-loop-lane-d-packaging/` | Lane D packaging profile for `deep-loop-runtime` + `--self-target` guard | Draft |\n| 012 | `012-push-wave-fanout/` | `depends_on`/`touches` schema + `flat_pool` guard; wave planner interface stub (not activated) | Draft |\n\n### Phase Transition Rules\n\n- Each phase MUST pass `validate.sh` independently before the next phase begins\n- Parent spec tracks aggregate progress via this map\n- Use `/speckit:resume [parent-folder]/[NNN-phase]/` to resume a specific phase\n- Run `validate.sh --recursive` on parent to validate all phases as an integrated unit\n\n### Phase Handoff Criteria\n\n| From | To | Criteria | Verification |\n|------|-----|----------|--------------|\n| 001 | 002 | `minIterations` guard in config and YAML; `min_iterations_guard_pass` event present | validate.sh on 001 |\n| 002 | 003 | ADR document present; parity test green on current code | validate.sh on 002 |\n| 003 | 004 | All four mode configs have `antiConvergence` block; optimizer invariant group rejects violations | validate.sh on 003 |\n| 004 | 005 | `research/inbox.jsonl` schema frozen; reducer reads inbox with `origin` propagation | validate.sh on 004 |\n| 005 | 006 | `resolveQuestionConflicts()` implemented; `question_conflict` event emitted on disagreement | validate.sh on 005 |\n| 006 | 007 | Bounded rejected index in place; exact + fuzzy check before candidates | validate.sh on 006 |\n| 007 | 008 | Three-part idea lifecycle events in JSONL; reducer owns promotion | validate.sh on 007 |\n| 008 | 009 | Coverage graph seeded before first convergence check; seeded nodes carry metadata | validate.sh on 008 |\n| 009 | 010 | `outcomeScoreDelta` gate in promotion; helped/hurt in benchmark report | validate.sh on 009 |\n| 010 | 011 | Two-phase promotion; `rollback-candidate.cjs` present | validate.sh on 010 |\n| 011 | 012 | `deep-loop-runtime.json` profile validates; `--self-target` guard in command | validate.sh on 011 |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-map -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 4. OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- The convergence-profile unification ADR (002) must precede the cross-mode contract (003) in ratification order; if 002 takes longer than expected, can 003 proceed with a provisional profile shape?\n- The push-wave fan-out (012) is dependency-last; if the conflict-safety substrate is not delivered by other teams in time, should 012's schema+guard deliverables still ship to unblock future activation?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n\n---\n\n## RELATED DOCUMENTS\n\n- **Phase children**: See `[0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/` sub-folders for per-phase spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n- **Source research**: `../../../001-reference-research/research/research.md` §5.2\n- **Parent Spec**: `../../spec.md` (123-agent-loops-improved)\n- **Graph Metadata**: See `graph-metadata.json` for `derived.last_active_child_id` pointer\n\n<!-- SCAFFOLD_VALIDATION_COUNTS:\nREQ-003\nREQ-004\nREQ-005\nREQ-006\nREQ-007\nREQ-008\n**Given**\n**Given**\n**Given**\n**Given**\n**Given**\n**Given**\n-->","lineStart":100,"lineEnd":173,"totalLines":173,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/spec.md","time":{"start":1782884281135,"end":1782884281139}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09d4a254d70232d4016a44a7b70e748191b40bac512d0ed64c"}},"id":"prt_f1c2f230a0014ukyI6UEqRUBmD","sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","messageID":"msg_f1c2f110d001W1OScOaPVSBMDE"}}
