\"id\": \"P1-002\",\n      \"severity\": \"P1\",\n      \"dimension\": \"fanout-lineage-isolation\",\n      \"title\": \"Unrecoverable iteration salvage can still produce a fulfilled lineage when the summary report exists\",\n      \"file\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1416\",\n      \"disposition\": \"active\",\n      \"content_hash\": \"sha256:p1-002-unrecoverable-salvage-fulfilled-lineage\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Reject or retry a lineage when salvage.failed > 0 unless every state-log iteration has a non-marker iteration markdown file; attach salvage summary to the thrown error so salvage_miss classification runs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"P1-003\",\n      \"severity\": \"P1\",\n      \"dimension\": \"correctness\",\n      \"title\": \"Mixed salvage/missing-artifact failures skip the transient retry path\",\n      \"file\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs:176\",\n      \"disposition\": \"active\",\n      \"content_hash\": \"sha256:p1-003-mixed-salvage-missing-artifact-skips-retry\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Classify any salvage.failed > 0 lineage-artifact failure as retryable unless an explicit fatal exit class is present, or attach a separate missingArtifacts/artifact_miss retry signal; add a regression where one iteration is salvaged but the top-level expected artifact remains missing and the retry succeeds.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"P1-004\",\n      \"severity\": \"P1\",\n      \"dimension\": \"security\",\n      \"title\": \"Detached OpenCode lineages run with prompt-only write isolation\",\n      \"file\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1084\",\n      \"disposition\": \"active\",\n      \"content_hash\": \"sha256:p1-004-detached-opencode-prompt-only-write-isolation\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Stop using --dangerously-skip-permissions for detached cli-opencode review lineages unless an equivalent path-scoped sandbox is active; pass the strongest available sandbox/workdir flags, allow sandboxMode where supported, and make unsafe fallback opt-in with a fatal warning for review fan-out.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"P1-005\",\n      \"severity\": \"P1\",\n      \"dimension\": \"traceability\",\n      \"title\": \"Fan-out adversarial playbook claims exit-0/no-artifact coverage, but the referenced regression never exercises that path\",\n      \"file\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-salvage-recovery.md:86\",\n      \"disposition\": \"active\",\n      \"content_hash\": \"sha256:p1-005-fanout-playbook-exit0-coverage-untested\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Add or repoint the regression to an exit-0/no-artifact case using the existing no-artifact stub, assert it is classified/retried/failed as documented, and update the playbook only after the exact bug-under-guard path is covered.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"P1-006\",\n      \"severity\": \"P1\",\n      \"dimension\": \"maintainability\",\n      \"title\": \"009 remediation parent is marked complete while its parent docs still contain scaffolds and pending child states\",\n      \"file\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/008-loop-systems-remediation/spec.md:18\",\n      \"disposition\": \"active\",\n      \"content_hash\": \"sha256:p1-006-remediation-parent-stale-scaffolds\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Regenerate/finalize the 009 parent spec, tasks, and implementation summary from the completed child docs, replace every scaffold placeholder and pending phase-map row, and rerun metadata backfill so parent status matches child evidence.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"P1-007\",\n      \"severity\": \"P1\",\n      \"dimension\": \"resource-map-coverage\",\n      \"title\": \"Parent and remediation discovery metadata omit the fan-out/remediation implementation surfaces operators must resume\",\n      \"file\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/graph-metadata.json:48\",\n      \"disposition\": \"active\",\n      \"content_hash\": \"sha256:p1-007-parent-remediation-discovery-metadata-omits-surfaces\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Backfill parent and 009 discovery artifacts so key_files and/or resource maps include the deep-loop runtime fan-out files, deep-loop workflow files, deep/speckit command surfaces, and remediation child docs; regenerate graph metadata from finalized packet docs after the stale 009 parent is repaired.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"P2-009-001\",\n      \"severity\": \"P2\",\n      \"dimension\": \"observability\",\n      \"title\": \"Lag-ceiling observability events normalize to unknown status\",\n      \"file\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:244\",\n      \"disposition\": \"active\",\n      \"content_hash\": \"sha256:p2-009-lag-ceiling-events-unknown-status\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Map lag_ceiling_exceeded and lag_ceiling_abort to typed warning/failed-or-retrying statuses and add a normalized observability event regression assertion.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"P1-011-001\",\n      \"severity\": \"P1\",\n      \"dimension\": \"synthesis-readiness\",\n      \"title\": \"Leaf-only GLM lineage is skipped by registry-only fan-out merge\",\n      \"file\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs:717\",\n      \"disposition\": \"active\",\n      \"content_hash\": \"sha256:p1-011-leaf-only-lineage-skipped-by-registry-only-merge\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Before synthesis/merge, run the reducer to reconstruct the lineage registry from JSONL or teach fanout-merge.cjs to consume leaf-only review state when registry files are intentionally absent; then assert the merged output carries all active GLM findings.\",\n      \"lineage_local_mitigation\": \"Synthesis reconciled this lineage by writing a registry from JSONL findingDetails; the underlying merge-path issue remains for other leaf-only lineages.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"note\": \"Iteration 011 completed with a JSONL delta and iteration-011.md (CONDITIONAL). All 11 iterations are verified.\"\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":105,"totalLines":105,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/review/lineages/glm/deep-review-findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1782884517242,"end":1782884517254}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_037826d108750b04016a44a8a519ec81919feeabb22e77f3e7"}},"id":"prt_f1c32c572001wBlUgmxdE4u2qv","sessionID":"ses_0e3d47d8bffeJ9bmuc4AVIwhXC","messageID":"msg_f1c32639e001eG3MlcaC7YQLxC"}}
