n expected, can 003 proceed with a provisional profile shape?\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/012-push-wave-fanout/tasks.md:\n  Line 24:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/007-ideas-backlog-lifecycle/spec.md:\n  Line 26:     completion_pct: 0\n\n  Line 44: | **Status** | Complete |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/010-deep-improvement-accepted-vs-shipped/spec.md:\n  Line 26:     completion_pct: 0\n\n  Line 44: | **Status** | Complete |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/003-cross-mode-anti-convergence-adr/spec.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Cross-Mode Anti-Convergence Contract ADR\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"antiConvergence contract ADR\"\n\n  Line 26:     completion_pct: 0\n\n  Line 31: # Cross-Mode Anti-Convergence Contract ADR\n\n  Line 44: | **Status** | Complete |\n\n  Line 157: | Dependency | Requires 002-convergence-profile-unification-adr to be ratified so `convergenceMode` semantics are stable before the invariant group is written | High | Do not write the optimizer invariant group until 002 ADR is locked |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/007-ideas-backlog-lifecycle/plan.md:\n  Line 25:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/010-deep-improvement-accepted-vs-shipped/plan.md:\n  Line 25:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/001-anti-convergence-floor/spec.md:\n  Line 26:     completion_pct: 0\n\n  Line 44: | **Status** | Complete |\n\n  Line 105: - Convergence math unification ADR — handled in 002-convergence-profile-unification-adr\n\n  Line 152: | Dependency | Convergence-profile unification ADR (002) must not contradict this field's semantics | Med | Coordinate field names with 002 author; `minIterations` is already the canonical name in both references |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/003-cross-mode-anti-convergence-adr/plan.md:\n  Line 25:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/001-anti-convergence-floor/plan.md:\n  Line 25:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/010-deep-improvement-accepted-vs-shipped/tasks.md:\n  Line 24:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/007-ideas-backlog-lifecycle/tasks.md:\n  Line 24:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/002-convergence-profile-unification-adr/decision-record.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"ADR: Convergence Profile Unification (shared schema, not one formula)\"\n\n  Line 11: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: decision-record-core | v2.2 -->\n\n  Line 12: # ADR: Convergence Profile Unification\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/003-cross-mode-anti-convergence-adr/tasks.md:\n  Line 24:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/001-anti-convergence-floor/tasks.md:\n  Line 24:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/002-convergence-profile-unification-adr/spec.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Convergence Math Unification ADR\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Convergence math is fracturing across three files (convergence.cjs, lib/council/convergence.cjs, coverage-graph-signals.ts) with no shared contract. Adding new signals to any one risks silent inconsistency with the others. An ADR must freeze the shared profile shape before more signals accrete.\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"convergence math ADR\"\n\n  Line 17:     next_safe_action: \"Draft the ADR document and parity test before any migration\"\n\n  Line 27:     completion_pct: 0\n\n  Line 32: # Convergence Math Unification ADR\n\n  Line 45: | **Status** | Complete |\n\n  Line 52: | **Handoff Criteria** | ADR document present and passes validate.sh; shared parity test runs green on current (pre-migration) code; profile schema fields named and typed |\n\n  Line 62: **Scope Boundary**: Record the ADR and pin a shared parity test. Actual migration of all callers to the new profile shape is a follow-up deep-rewrite outside this packet.\n\n  Line 68: - ADR document recording the decision (shared profile shape, per-loop metric semantics, rejected alternative)\n\n  Line 86: Record an ADR defining a declarative convergence profile (`threshold/weight/role/direction/normalizer`) with a shared parity test pinning current traces before migration begins; the ADR explicitly rejects one universal convergence formula (per-loop metric semantics are preserved; only the profile shape is shared).\n\n  Line 97: - ADR document recording the decision (profile shape, per-loop metric semantics, rejected alternatives)\n\n  Line 105: - Changing any convergence behavior — this is ADR + test-pin only\n\n  Line 111: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` | Modify | Add profile schema comment block and exported profile type; cross-reference to ADR |\n\n  Line 112: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/convergence.cjs` | Modify | Add profile schema comment block and cross-reference to ADR |\n\n  Line 126: | REQ-001 | ADR records the decision: one shared profile shape (`threshold/weight/role/direction/normalizer`), per-loop metric semantics preserved, one universal formula explicitly rejected | ADR document present; all five profile fields named and typed; rejected alternative documented with rationale |\n\n  Line 140: - **SC-001**: ADR is present, all `[...]` placeholders replaced, and `validate.sh` passes; profile schema is documented with `threshold/weight/role/direction/normalizer` fields named and typed; the decision explicitly rejects a single universal formula\n\n  Line 151: | Risk | Migration is rated hard; the ADR is only the decision step — premature migration before the ADR is ratified could create conflicting schemas | High | This phase ends at ADR + parity test; migration is a separate follow-up packet |\n\n  Line 152: | Risk | Parity test might reveal existing bugs in current convergence math, triggering unplanned changes | Med | Pin current behavior as the baseline even if imperfect; note discrepancies as open issues in the ADR |\n\n  Line 161: - What is the right `normalizer` function per loop type — identity for research, Bayesian for council, decay-weighted for coverage? This must be decided in the ADR before migration starts.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/010-deep-improvement-accepted-vs-shipped/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 22:     completion_pct: 100\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/003-cross-mode-anti-convergence-adr/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 22:     completion_pct: 100\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/002-convergence-profile-unification-adr/plan.md:\n  Line 25:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/001-anti-convergence-floor/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 22:     completion_pct: 100\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/005-anchor-ownership-conflict-adr/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 22:     completion_pct: 100\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/009-loop-quality-benchmark/spec.md:\n  Line 26:     completion_pct: 0\n\n  Line 44: | **Status** | Complete |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/009-loop-quality-benchmark/tasks.md:\n  Line 24:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/009-loop-quality-benchmark/plan.md:\n  Line 25:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/003-deep-loop-workflows/002-convergence-profile-unification-adr/tasks.md:\n  Line 24:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-lo